<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="129" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Main characteristics.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="129">Shell ovate-conic or turreted, glossy in general, with or without spiral lirae on the first 1-2 whorls, first whorl rounded, body whorl broad, columella truncated. Vagina shorter than penis. The proximal part of male reproductive organ varies with respect to the form of the flagellum, i.e. from a comb-like structure with many notches, to a hand-like structure with two or more finger-like processes (Figs 3-5).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
